            <h2>Refund policy </h2>
            <p class="text-justify">With reference to the Air New Zealand Airline’s <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/refund-policy.aspx">refund policy</a>, if you cancel your flight ticket within 24 hours of booking, the airline will refund its entire flight cost without any deduction. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">If airline cancels your <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/">flight ticket</a>, the airline will either refund the unused flight fare or shift you to another flight. However, if you miss the flight, the airline will not be liable for any kind of refund on having failed to inform the airline. </p>
            <h3>Frequently asked question</h3>

            <h3 class="text-justify">Who can receive a refund with Air New Zealand Airlines? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">If you have purchased the ticket, you are eligible to receive a refund. You must provide necessary documents confirming that you have paid for the ticket such as an invoice or credit card. However, if the person who paid for the ticket couldn’t collect refund due to sickness or death, the refund will be issued to an immediate family member, subject to the person providing a death certificate or medical certificate. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How to cancel a flight ticket with Air New Zealand Airlines? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">If you wish to cancel the flight ticket, you may call the Air New Zealand Airlines customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. Also, you can visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How can I make the request for a refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">In order to make a request for a refund, you can visit the official website of Air New Zealand Airlines and fill out the refund request form. It may take 7 to 10 business days for the refund to reflect on your card/bank statement. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Can I ask for compensation if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">There can be a possibility that your replacement flight delays your arrival by 2 or more hours or your flight was canceled less than 14 days before departure, you are eligible to get compensation. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Is my flight refundable? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">Though such information is mentioned on the ticket, you can check if your flight is refundable by visiting the official website of the airline and entering the ticket or document number. It will display refund eligibility and information. </p>

